&lt;p&gt;Inflection AI, Inc. created Pi, the world’s first emotionally intelligent AI, to help people work through decisions, emotions, and challenges. Pi is a personal AI agent that is pro-social, empathetic, and contextually aware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity to join a high-growth AI company as Inflection AI&#39;s first hire in Ireland and a critical member of our global Safety, Wellbeing &amp;amp; Trust team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for shaping and leading the company’s strategy and approach to privacy, regulatory, and corporate compliance–including GDPR, the EU AI Act, and other applicable regulations–while also ensuring consistent, effective day-to-day enforcement of our content and safety policies worldwide. In this role, you will be instrumental in establishing our presence in Ireland and ensuring that our products, operations, and teams scale responsibly and safely anchored in our public benefit mission, values, legal obligations, and commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a leader with strong judgment, credibility, and executive presence — someone equally comfortable navigating policy, operations, regulatory engagement, and cross-functional decision-making in a fast-moving, high-growth environment as well as detail-oriented, execution-focused and operational work.&lt;/p&gt;
